# Hawk-256
# Weak-key M-S-UEO counterexample.
# Recipe: q00 = constant polynomial 1, q01 = constant polynomial a for a in {0, 1, 2, 16},
#         salt = all zeros, s1 = constant polynomial 0, message fixed.
# Same encoded (msg, sig) verifies under multiple distinct malformed public keys.
# Falsifies M-S-UEO (malicious-strong-universal-exclusive-ownership) over malformed pks.
# WARNING: each pk is malformed; not from honest keygen.

